.TH MFUTIL-ALL 1 2025-01-01 "mfutil 0.1.1"
.SH NAME
mfutil-all \- Run all music library management tasks
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mfutil all
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B all
subcommand runs a comprehensive suite of music library management tasks
in sequence. It performs syncing, organization, artwork processing, and
symlink creation to fully optimize your music collection.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-music-dir " " \fIPATH\fR
Specify the music directory path (default: ~/Music)
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-skip " " \fISUBCOMMANDS\fR
Comma-separated list of subcommands to skip (available: sync,art,albums,tracks,organize,reorganize,import)
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help information
.SH OPERATION SEQUENCE
.TP
1. Sync tags with MusicBrainz
.TP
2. Extract/process artist album art
.TP
3. Set folder icons
.TP
4. Extract album art
.TP
5. Create album symlinks
.TP
6. Create track symlinks
.TP
7. Organize music library
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run all tasks on default music directory:
.B mfutil all
.TP
Run all tasks except sync and art:
.B mfutil all --skip sync,art
.TP
Run all tasks on custom directory:
.B mfutil all --music-dir /path/to/music
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mfutil (1),
.BR mfutil-sync (1),
.BR mfutil-art (1),
.BR mfutil-albums (1),
.BR mfutil-tracks (1)
.SH NOTES
This command can take significant time for large music libraries.
Use --skip to customize the operations performed.